        <heading>2782.  Termination of annuity; absence of a designated term</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2782.  Termination of annuity; absence of a designated term
In the absence of a designated term, an annuity established in favor of a natural person terminates upon the death of that person, but one in favor of a juridical person is without effect.</p>
        </content>
